CPP-GPENGINE RELEASES HOW-TO
============================
For package mantainers only!
============================
Author: Pablo Garcia Gonzalez
Date: 11.11.2003

1. Do a tag with the corresponding release label. For releasing,
   for example, a version 1.0.4, the tag should be "RELEASE_1_0_4".

2. Export the module files into a different local directory in order
   to get a clean copy of the source files without the CVS directories:

   $> cvs export -r RELEASE_1_0_4 cpp-gpengine

3. Pack the all module files into two different compressed files, tar.gz 
   (for linux/unix releases) and .zip (for windows releases)

   $> tar -cvf cpp-gpengine-src-1.0.4.tar cpp-gpengine/
   $> gzip cpp-gpengine-src-1.0.4.tar
   $> zip -r cpp-gpengine-src-1.0.4.zip cpp-gpengine/

4) Transfer these two files to ftp://upload.sourceforge.net using
   an anonymous/e-mail user.


5) Add the files to a release using the sourceforge admin tool.

   http://sourceforge.net/project/admin/?group_id=62780
 
    
